
12. Functional Requirements Documentation - Document FR-01 through FR-n with acceptance criteria
The functional requirements define the core capabilities that the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System must provide to enable effective incident reporting, tracking, response coordination, and compliance management.
FR-01: Incident Reporting
Description:
The system shall allow employees and authorized users to report cybersecurity incidents through a standardized digital form.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	User can successfully submit an incident report
•	Incident details (type, description, timestamp) are captured
•	A unique incident ID is generated
•	Incident is stored in the centralized system

FR-02: Incident Severity Classification

Description:
The system shall automatically classify incidents based on severity levels such as low, medium, high, or critical.

Acceptance Criteria:
•	Severity is assigned based on predefined rules
•	Severity level is visible to SOC analysts and administrators
•	Classification occurs immediately after incident submission
FR-03: Incident Tracking and Status Management
Description:
The system shall track incidents throughout their lifecycle, from detection to resolution.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Incident status updates are recorded (New, In Progress, Resolved, Closed)
•	Status changes are visible in real time
•	Incident history is maintained without data loss
FR-04: Guided Response Workflow
Description:
The system shall provide structured response workflows to assist SOC teams in managing incidents.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Workflow steps are displayed based on incident severity
•	SOC analysts can follow and update response steps
•	Completion of each step is recorded in the system
FR-05: Notification and Alert Management
Description:
The system shall notify relevant stakeholders when incidents are reported or updated.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Alerts are triggered on incident creation or status change
•	Notifications reach assigned SOC analysts and administrators
•	Alert information is clear and accurate
FR-06: User Authentication and Role-Based Access
Description:
The system shall provide secure authentication and role-based access control for users.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Only authorized users can access the system
•	Users are assigned roles (Reporter, SOC Analyst, Admin)
•	Unauthorized access attempts are denied
FR-07: Administrative Dashboard
Description:
The system shall provide an administrative dashboard for real-time monitoring and management of incidents.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Admin can view incident statistics and severity distribution
•	Admin can assign incidents and manage user roles
•	Dashboard updates in real time
FR-08: Audit Trail and Report Generation
Description:
The system shall generate audit logs and compliance reports for accountability and regulatory purposes.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	All incident actions are logged with timestamps and user details
•	Reports can be generated for audits and reviews
•	Reports can be viewed and downloaded securely
